{
  "Election": {
    "election_id": "x4dkfd",
    "title": "BV2193 — Bullet Voting Backfires (1 of 2) — the honest ballots elect the compromise",
    "description": "From the exercises set of the STAR education repo (github.com/masiarek/star-voting-library, 01_STAR/exercises/) — predict-then-peek problems with hidden solutions; this election is the live, vote-able copy of its exercise. The strategy pair's base case (exercise ex06): nine voters, three speakers — 4×(Ari 5, Bree 3, Cash 0), 4×(Cash 5, Bree 2, Ari 0), 1×(Bree 5, Cash 1). With Ari's fans voting honestly, the scoring round is Bree 25, Cash 21, Ari 20 — and the broad compromise Bree beats Cash 5-4 in the runoff. The fans' honest 3s are exactly what put their second choice on the podium. Part 2 (BV2194) reruns the election after those four fans bullet vote, hoping to lift Ari — and elects their nightmare. Side lesson the ranked races add: on these same honest opinions RCV-IRV eliminates Bree (1 first choice) and elects Cash — the compromise STAR finds, IRV can't even see; Ranked Robin agrees with STAR (Bree is the Condorcet winner). LH-verified.",
